Gazprom, Mechel, Polyus Gold: Russian Equity Preview

-- B y   Y u l i y a   F e d o r i n o v a
-- 
2011-08-01T04:00:00Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-07-31/gazprom-mechel-polyus-gold-russian-equity-preview.html
The following companies may be active
in Russian trading. Stock symbols are in parentheses and share
prices are from the previous close.  The 30-stock  Micex Index (INDEXCF)  fell 0.9 percent to 1,705.18. The
dollar-denominated RTS Index declined 1 percent to 1,965.02.  OAO Gazprom (GAZP RX): Gazprom is in talks to buy a stake
in British  power plants  in Nottinghamshire,  England , owned by
RWE AG, the Sunday Times reported, without saying where it got
the information. Shares of  Russia ’s largest gas producer fell
1.3 percent to 199.36 rubles.  OAO  Mechel (MTLR)  : Workers at BHP Billiton Ltd.’s coking-
coal mines in  Australia , the world’s largest exporter of the
steelmaking ingredient, resumed strikes on July 31 as labor
unions prepare for the last two rounds of talks with management.
American depositary receipts of  Mechel (MTL) , Russia’s largest coking-
coal exporter, rose for the first day in three, climbing 0.1
percent to $24.88.  Polyus Gold International Ltd. (POLG LI): Gold futures rose
to a record $1,637.50 an ounce on demand for an investment haven
amid mounting concern over the U.S. debt-limit impasse and signs
of a faltering economy. Polyus shares rose 0.9 percent to $3.55.  To contact the reporters on this story:
